      "side": 1,
      "message": "File: CombinedOauth2AuthenticationFilter.java:91,101\n  Issue: config.parseUser(request) is called twice per proxy-auth request — once in isLoginAttempt() and again in createToken(). Shiro\u0027s onAccessDenied calls them\n    sequentially on the same request. The full header parsing + validation runs twice needlessly. If X-Forwarded-User validation is expensive or produces side-effects\n    (logging warnings), this matters.\n  Severity: Major\n  Recommendation: Cache the result as a request attribute (e.g. request.setAttribute(PARSED_USER_KEY, user)) in isLoginAttempt, read it back in createToken.",
      "revId": "2babd2d393d8b271138ec94216b3e2a9ff4071c4",
      "serverId": "7fc14799-209e-464c-9743-7a06c2c21a81"
